[?] CLI MAP: asusctl fan-curve
-------------------------------------------------------------------
$ asusctl fan-curve --help
Usage: asusctl fan-curve [--get-enabled] [--default] [--mod-profile <mod-profile>] [--enable-fan-curves <enable-fan-curves>] [--enable-fan-curve <enable-fan-curve>] [--fan <fan>] [--data <data>]

fan curve commands

Options:
  --get-enabled     get enabled fan profiles
  --default         set the active profile's fan curve to default
  --mod-profile     profile to modify fan-curve for. shows data if no options
                    provided
  --enable-fan-curves
                    enable or disable <true/false> fan all curves for a profile;
                    --mod_profile required
  --enable-fan-curve
                    enable or disable <true/false> a single fan curve for a
                    profile; --mod_profile and --fan required
  --fan             select fan <cpu/gpu/mid> to modify; --mod_profile required
  --data            data format = 30c:1%,49c:2%,...; --mod-profile required. If
                    '%' is omitted the fan range is 0-255
  --help, help      display usage information

